<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-18T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-18T03:00:00-05:00" n="717" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">123 M 956/293: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-18T10:00:00+02:00">December 18, 1940—10 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1153. For the Under Secretary. I am departing from Vichy on December
                                18 by commercial plane for Dakar via Algiers. General Weygand now in
                                Dakar will leave there for Casablanca on December 22 and will
                                receive me on December 21. I shall then return to Algiers,
                                thereafter visiting Tunis, Casablanca, Rabat, and Tangier in the
                                order named, planning to spend 2 or 3 days or longer in each place
                                depending on the circumstances.</p>
                            <p>Matthews in charge.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>